CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 27, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "The Glamorous Cotillion - Scenes from the third annual debutante Cotillion given by Pittsburgh AKAs include...Center, the glamorous debutantes of 1954 pose for the photographer..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nine debutantes wearing light colored evening gowns, including one seated in center wearing light colored strapless gown with dark sheer overlay and sheer wrap, posed in room of Syria Mosque for Alpha Kappa Alpha's 1954 Cotillion
